&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Let&#39;s start with the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As our &lt;strong&gt;Affiliate Team Manager for LATAM&lt;/strong&gt;, you will own the strategic direction and commercial performance of Betano&#39;s affiliate ecosystem across the region, with direct responsibility for Spanish-speaking LATAM markets and a dotted-line remit over Brazil. &amp;nbsp;Leading a team of Affiliate Managers, you will set the regional agenda, design the commercial framework, and drive scalable, compliant, ROI-positive growth across one of Kaizen Gaming&#39;s most strategic geographies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As an Affiliate Team Manager&amp;nbsp; you will&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the LATAM affiliate strategy end-to-end, setting regional priorities, commercial models, and growth targets aligned with Kaizen Gaming&#39;s broader market ambitions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, coach, and develop a team of Affiliate Managers across LATAM, establishing clear performance standards and operating cadence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide dotted-line support over the Brazilian affiliate operation, ensuring alignment on strategy, commercial frameworks, governance, and performance benchmarks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and negotiate complex commercial agreements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive performance optimization across the regional portfolio, holding accountability for main KPIs at country and portfolio level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Country Managers to translate market-level strategy into affiliate execution, and act as the regional commercial authority on affiliate matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and govern the regional tooling and process stack: affiliate platforms, attribution and tracking, BI and reporting, fraud prevention, and compliance tooling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own affiliate compliance and risk management across LATAM, working with Legal and Compliance to ensure adherence to local regulatory frameworks and embedding safeguards against reputational, regulatory, and financial exposure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish regional governance: contract standards, approval thresholds, payment controls, audit trails, and onboarding protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead senior partner relationships, top-tier affiliates, content partners, strategic networks and creators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate affiliates department with the wider digital marketing ecosystem to identify cross-channel leverage and avoid cannibalisation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver regional performance reporting and insights to executive stakeholders, translating data into clear commercial decisions and forward-looking plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor the competitive landscape, regulatory shifts, and market-specific dynamics across LATAM, and translate signals into strategic moves.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A degree in Marketing, Business Administration, Management, Economics, or a related field (Master&#39;s degree a plus).&lt;/li

